For other uses, see Tin drum (disambiguation).The Tin Drum (German: Die Blechtrommel) is a 1959 novel by GÃ¼nter Grass. The novel is the first book of Grass's Danziger Trilogie (Danzig Trilogy). It was adapted into a 1979 film, which won both the Palme d'Or, in the same year, and the Academy Award for Best Foreign Language Film the following year.